
Macro: XDEFVAR

Syntax:   (XDEFVAR var1 &optional val2 doc3)

 (The syntax is identical to that of DEFVAR.)

Returns:

 Same as what DEFVAR returns.

Processing:

 XDEFVAR executes DEFVAR at RUN TIME
 (suitable for compiled initialization routines).

 Under the interpreter, XDEFVAR is identical to DEFVAR, except that
 it may be used in places where DEFVAR is not allowed (i.e. at other
 than "top level").

 See DEFVAR for more information.

Errors signalled:

 See DEFVAR.

Notes:

 See ZEVDVAR and ZEVXVAR for more information.

